        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued May 6 at 3:06PM PDT until May 6 at 4:30PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 306 PM PDT, Gauge reports indicated thunderstorms producing heavy
rain across the warned area. Flash flooding is ongoing or expected
to begin shortly.

HAZARD...Life-threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Gauges reported.

IMPACT...Life-threatening flash flooding of low-water crossings,
creeks, normally dry washes and roads.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Henderson, Boulder City, Lake Las Vegas, Las Vegas Bay, Sam Boyd
Stadium, Green Valley, East Las Vegas, Railroad Pass, Las Vegas
Bay Campground, Boulder Beach and Boulder Beach Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
